*In [[zoology]], a '''hibernaculum''' is the location chosen by an animal for hibernation. Commonly this may be a [[hibernation|hibernating]] [[mammal]] or [[insect]].

*In [[botany]], a '''hibernaculum''' is a bud, case, or protective covering that a plant uses to survive the challenging environmental conditions during a dormancy period.

* "hibernaculum"(hi-buhr-NAK-yuh-luhm) noun, also hibernacle.

